{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/work/minimal-mistakes-jekyll-theme/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Minimal Mistakes","date":"2016-04-15T00:00:00.000Z","date_pretty":"April 15th, 2016","date_from_now":"4 years ago","last_modified_at":"2020-01-13T17:25:41.000Z","last_modified_at_from_now":"6 months ago","path":"/work/minimal-mistakes-jekyll-theme/","author":null,"excerpt":"A flexible two-column Jekyll theme.","tags":["Jekyll","web development","design","open source","GitHub"],"image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"aspectRatio":1.7741935483870968,"src":"/static/fdfedffa0cd9f1b85baa15ef43451be7/fc20c/minimal-mistakes-3-feature.jpg","srcSet":"/static/fdfedffa0cd9f1b85baa15ef43451be7/6e883/minimal-mistakes-3-feature.jpg 275w,\n/static/fdfedffa0cd9f1b85baa15ef43451be7/a09ef/minimal-mistakes-3-feature.jpg 550w,\n/static/fdfedffa0cd9f1b85baa15ef43451be7/fc20c/minimal-mistakes-3-feature.jpg 1100w,\n/static/fdfedffa0cd9f1b85baa15ef43451be7/9352a/minimal-mistakes-3-feature.jpg 1600w","sizes":"(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px"},"fixed":{"src":"/static/fdfedffa0cd9f1b85baa15ef43451be7/fc20c/minimal-mistakes-3-feature.jpg","height":619,"width":1100}}},"toc":true,"comments":false,"comments_locked":null,"hide_meta":true},"id":"a72d3553-d065-520f-a6b0-964e5298c8eb","html":"<p>Minimal Mistakes is a flexible two-column Jekyll theme. Perfect for hosting your personal site, blog, or portfolio on GitHub or your own server. </p>\n<p>Includes responsive layouts (single, archive index, search, splash, and paginated home page) that look great on mobile and desktop browsers. As the name implies — styling is purposely minimalistic to be enhanced and customized by you.</p>\n<p>\n  <a href=\"https://mmistakes.github.io/minimal-mistakes/\" class=\"btn\">Live preview</a>\n</p>\n<h2 id=\"notable-features\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#notable-features\" aria-label=\"notable features permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Notable features</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Bundled as a “theme gem” for easier installation/upgrading.</li>\n<li>Support for Jekyll’s built-in Sass/SCSS preprocessor.</li>\n<li>Nine different skins (color variations).</li>\n<li>Optional <a href=\"https://mmistakes.github.io/minimal-mistakes/docs/layouts/#headers\">header images</a>, <a href=\"https://mmistakes.github.io/minimal-mistakes/docs/layouts/#sidebars\">custom sidebars</a>, <a href=\"https://mmistakes.github.io/minimal-mistakes/docs/helpers/#table-of-contents\">table of contents</a>, <a href=\"https://mmistakes.github.io/minimal-mistakes/docs/helpers/#gallery\">galleries</a>, related posts, <a href=\"https://mmistakes.github.io/minimal-mistakes/docs/configuration/#breadcrumb-navigation-beta\">breadcrumb links</a>, <a href=\"https://mmistakes.github.io/minimal-mistakes/docs/helpers/#navigation-list\">navigation lists</a>, and more.</li>\n<li>Commenting support (powered by <a href=\"https://disqus.com/\">Disqus</a>, <a href=\"https://developers.facebook.com/docs/plugins/comments\">Facebook</a>, Google+, <a href=\"https://www.discourse.org/\">Discourse</a>, static-based via <a href=\"https://staticman.net/\">Staticman</a>, and <a href=\"https://utteranc.es/\">utterances</a>).</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"browser-frame\">\n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 1100px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 96.36363636363636%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\" alt=\"Minimal Mistakes splash layout\" title=\"Minimal Mistakes splash layout\" data-src=\"/static/d548408869822563e7a729f50afe3674/eacc7/mm-layout-splash.jpg\" data-srcset=\"/static/d548408869822563e7a729f50afe3674/16841/mm-layout-splash.jpg 275w,\n/static/d548408869822563e7a729f50afe3674/50c97/mm-layout-splash.jpg 550w,\n/static/d548408869822563e7a729f50afe3674/eacc7/mm-layout-splash.jpg 1100w,\n/static/d548408869822563e7a729f50afe3674/b773b/mm-layout-splash.jpg 1442w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"browser-frame\">\n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 1100px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 58.909090909090914%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\" alt=\"Minimal Mistakes posts by year archive layout\" title=\"Minimal Mistakes posts by year archive layout\" data-src=\"/static/b2c9268de04490e4b0d9dcc3034ac28c/eacc7/mm-posts-archive-layout.jpg\" data-srcset=\"/static/b2c9268de04490e4b0d9dcc3034ac28c/16841/mm-posts-archive-layout.jpg 275w,\n/static/b2c9268de04490e4b0d9dcc3034ac28c/50c97/mm-posts-archive-layout.jpg 550w,\n/static/b2c9268de04490e4b0d9dcc3034ac28c/eacc7/mm-posts-archive-layout.jpg 1100w,\n/static/b2c9268de04490e4b0d9dcc3034ac28c/b773b/mm-posts-archive-layout.jpg 1442w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"browser-frame\">\n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 1100px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 138.1818181818182%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\" alt=\"Minimal Mistakes post layout\" title=\"Minimal Mistakes post layout\" data-src=\"/static/77b0884948a776ba2463e90e3b1b4fe8/eacc7/mm-post-layout.jpg\" data-srcset=\"/static/77b0884948a776ba2463e90e3b1b4fe8/16841/mm-post-layout.jpg 275w,\n/static/77b0884948a776ba2463e90e3b1b4fe8/50c97/mm-post-layout.jpg 550w,\n/static/77b0884948a776ba2463e90e3b1b4fe8/eacc7/mm-post-layout.jpg 1100w,\n/static/77b0884948a776ba2463e90e3b1b4fe8/b773b/mm-post-layout.jpg 1442w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"browser-frame\">\n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 1100px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 58.909090909090914%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\" alt=\"Minimal Mistakes post layout with sidebars\" title=\"Minimal Mistakes post layout with sidebars\" data-src=\"/static/7dcc7214d4c2f4b1855a95094ae8e1a2/eacc7/mm-post-layout-sidebars.jpg\" data-srcset=\"/static/7dcc7214d4c2f4b1855a95094ae8e1a2/16841/mm-post-layout-sidebars.jpg 275w,\n/static/7dcc7214d4c2f4b1855a95094ae8e1a2/50c97/mm-post-layout-sidebars.jpg 550w,\n/static/7dcc7214d4c2f4b1855a95094ae8e1a2/eacc7/mm-post-layout-sidebars.jpg 1100w,\n/static/7dcc7214d4c2f4b1855a95094ae8e1a2/b773b/mm-post-layout-sidebars.jpg 1442w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n</div>\n<h2 id=\"usage\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#usage\" aria-label=\"usage permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Usage</h2>\n<p>To learn more about how to customize this theme, include feature images in posts, modify the look and feel, create new posts, and some other junk, <a href=\"https://mmistakes.github.io/minimal-mistakes/docs/quick-start-guide/\">read up here</a>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"license\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#license\" aria-label=\"license permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>License</h2>\n<p>This theme is free and open source software, distributed under the <a href=\"https://github.com/mmistakes/minimal-mistakes/blob/master/LICENSE\">MIT License</a>.</p>","excerpt":"Minimal Mistakes is a flexible two-column Jekyll theme. Perfect for hosting your personal site, blog, or portfolio on GitHub or your own…","timeToRead":1,"tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/work/minimal-mistakes-jekyll-theme/#notable-features\">Notable features</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/work/minimal-mistakes-jekyll-theme/#usage\">Usage</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/work/minimal-mistakes-jekyll-theme/#license\">License</a></li>\n</ul>"},"comments":{"edges":[{"node":{"id":"3fa5c195-d40b-5658-a681-2346b1edef74","frontmatter":{"name":"Michael Rose","email":"1ce71bc10b86565464b612093d89707e","friendlyDate":"July 19, 2013","iso8601Date":"2013-07-19T13:59:23.000Z","published":true},"html":"<p>Thanks sir!</p>"}},{"node":{"id":"e5a28d15-1c4f-51e5-9533-a28f5f6055bc","frontmatter":{"name":"Lindsay Kay","email":null,"friendlyDate":"September 27, 2013","iso8601Date":"2013-09-27T19:35:27.000Z","published":null},"html":"<p>Michael - brilliant work, exactly what I needed. Typography spot on, clean code,\nflawless install. Thanks!</p>"}},{"node":{"id":"72c181da-e59f-5cd9-91c3-165edc82b6ad","frontmatter":{"name":"Michael Rose","email":"1ce71bc10b86565464b612093d89707e","friendlyDate":"September 27, 2013","iso8601Date":"2013-09-27T19:36:52.000Z","published":null},"html":"<p>Awesome. Glad it’s been useful.</p>"}},{"node":{"id":"385172b8-7880-5f2c-8a1e-c06bbd95d73d","frontmatter":{"name":"Lindsay Kay","email":null,"friendlyDate":"October 26, 2013","iso8601Date":"2013-10-26T18:29:29.000Z","published":null},"html":"<p>Minimal Mistakes in the wild:\n<a href=\"http://xeolabs.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://xeolabs.com</a></p>"}},{"node":{"id":"85759730-204d-54e1-9fcc-1de03080bad6","frontmatter":{"name":"zjxhz","email":null,"friendlyDate":"November 13, 2013","iso8601Date":"2013-11-13T08:55:03.000Z","published":null},"html":"<p>A simple yet beautiful theme, thanks! However, I would like to be able to\ncustomize the style a bit, for example I don’t like the indent of a new\nparagraph and its close margin to the previous one. So I had to comment out the\n<code class=\"language-text\">&quot;p+p&quot;</code> part in <code class=\"language-text\">main.min.css</code>. I’m very new to css, actually I had only spent\nless than a few hours to learn it today, so it was difficult for me to customize\nit further, e.g. to change the font of the posts, without a clear document.</p>\n<p>So my question is that is there a document associated with this <code class=\"language-text\">main.min.css</code>\nfile? Or at least can I find a pretty formatted one(formatting it with some\ntools led me to some errors)? I can only guess that it contains something from\n&#x3C;git.io/normalize> but they seem very different now, or it a combination of\nother css files too?</p>"}},{"node":{"id":"8b83042f-d292-5e1a-8cd0-8f6f17acc24e","frontmatter":{"name":"Michael Rose","email":"1ce71bc10b86565464b612093d89707e","friendlyDate":"November 13, 2013","iso8601Date":"2013-11-13T11:55:39.000Z","published":null},"html":"<p>I’ve created a few Jekyll themes after this one so forgive me if I jumble this\nup. They’re all starting to blend together to me now ;-)</p>\n<p>The typography in this theme was heavily based off of Typeplate’s set of styles.\nI liked the indents and no padding around paragraphs because it mimic the\ntypography of most books, which is a feel I was going for.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://typeplate.com\">Typeplate</a> has since dropped support for LESS, so I\nremoved it for the most part and incorporated a few mixins as a base to build\noff of.</p>\n<p>If you’re new to CSS then there’s a lot going on with the theme that I can’t\neasily explain in a comment. To further complicate it I use LESS to build all of\nthe stylesheets, which are broken up into smaller chunks and preprocessed to\noutput <code class=\"language-text\">main.min.css</code>. That’s another layer of abstraction that you’d have to\nget familiar with on top of learning CSS.</p>\n<p>But if you take a look at the .less files you’ll see they’re much more logical\nthan digging through <code class=\"language-text\">main.min.css</code> which has been optimized for speed by\nremoving extra spaces and comments. The .less files have more documentation to\nhelp customize. For the most part if you bump around <code class=\"language-text\">typography.less</code>,\n<code class=\"language-text\">page.less</code>, and <code class=\"language-text\">variables.less</code> you should be able to do some simple\nmodifications to suit your taste.</p>"}},{"node":{"id":"00f214b4-8fd6-5415-b380-dc52f76d0b5d","frontmatter":{"name":"zjxhz","email":null,"friendlyDate":"November 13, 2013","iso8601Date":"2013-11-13T13:31:20.000Z","published":null},"html":"<p>Thanks for the quick reply! It seems to me now more clear and logical even I’m\nstill confused, but I’m happy already with the paragraph changes I’ve made and\nI’ll leave other customizations to future.</p>"}},{"node":{"id":"2a58c581-5416-5138-b97e-6153dccf74a2","frontmatter":{"name":"Luca","email":null,"friendlyDate":"October 04, 2014","iso8601Date":"2014-10-04T16:31:24.000Z","published":null},"html":"<p>This is a beautiful theme!! One question, if possible.</p>\n<p>I want to change the home page, so that it contains the list of posts instead of\nrecent posts (like your theme “hpstr”)</p>\n<p>Is it possible? If yes, how?</p>\n<p>Thank you very much.</p>"}},{"node":{"id":"2dbc7ccb-de94-56cc-a808-b6ee28e89d73","frontmatter":{"name":"Michael Rose","email":"1ce71bc10b86565464b612093d89707e","friendlyDate":"October 04, 2014","iso8601Date":"2014-10-04T18:49:05.000Z","published":null},"html":"<p>Anything is possible. You’ll have to modify <code class=\"language-text\">index.html</code> to pull in full posts\ninstead of just the title and excerpt.</p>\n<p>If you look at HPSTR you should be able to get some inspiration and modify the\n<a href=\"https://github.com/mmistakes/hpstr-jekyll-theme/blob/master/index.html\">homepage code</a>\nand apply it to the Minimal Mistakes theme.</p>"}},{"node":{"id":"68246328-7b05-5dc1-bf06-048279d67271","frontmatter":{"name":"Jordi Pont-Tuset","email":null,"friendlyDate":"October 09, 2014","iso8601Date":"2014-10-09T12:35:11.000Z","published":null},"html":"<p>Thanks a lot for this theme, I love it!</p>\n<p>You can check <a href=\"http://jponttuset.github.io\">my version here</a> :)</p>"}},{"node":{"id":"59bc3631-286f-58e6-9914-8212c8c564d1","frontmatter":{"name":"Clayton Burlison","email":null,"friendlyDate":"October 30, 2014","iso8601Date":"2014-10-30T23:50:40.000Z","published":null},"html":"<p>You have a bad link on this page. Under the “Usage” header, the “read up here”\nshould now link to <a href=\"https://mmistakes.github.io/minimal-mistakes/\">https://mmistakes.github.io/minimal-mistakes/</a>.</p>"}},{"node":{"id":"28f82dbf-4688-5287-87cb-7080c07c5a9e","frontmatter":{"name":"Michael Rose","email":"1ce71bc10b86565464b612093d89707e","friendlyDate":"October 31, 2014","iso8601Date":"2014-10-31T13:53:11.000Z","published":null},"html":"<p>Eagle eyes. Thanks for the bad link catch.</p>"}},{"node":{"id":"fa1eb67b-135b-5726-ae4f-37cbd5cd1198","frontmatter":{"name":"chippyash","email":null,"friendlyDate":"December 15, 2014","iso8601Date":"2014-12-15T18:16:48.000Z","published":null},"html":"<p>Thank you Michael - just started with it (and Jekyll.) Made setting up my Github\npage very easy and quick.</p>"}},{"node":{"id":"431164e1-a632-5afa-aa68-5934a4aa7533","frontmatter":{"name":"Luca","email":null,"friendlyDate":"December 18, 2014","iso8601Date":"2014-12-18T15:28:51.000Z","published":null},"html":"<p>Thanks for the advice! This is my first work with “minimal mistakes” theme (v.\n0.1 beta ;)).</p>"}},{"node":{"id":"a9eae832-bacb-5926-9849-cd5e86a4f625","frontmatter":{"name":"Brian Moseley","email":null,"friendlyDate":"January 12, 2015","iso8601Date":"2015-01-12T02:46:08.000Z","published":null},"html":"<p>Is it possible to create a dropdown “submenu” with this theme through the data\nfile and some alterations to <code class=\"language-text\">navigation.html</code>?</p>"}},{"node":{"id":"21b9f707-6ab1-51ea-84ba-b3af141c3b0f","frontmatter":{"name":"Michael Rose","email":"1ce71bc10b86565464b612093d89707e","friendlyDate":"January 12, 2015","iso8601Date":"2015-01-12T02:52:54.000Z","published":null},"html":"<p>It is possible if your CSS skills are strong. It’s tricky to do multi-leveled\nnavigation with Jekyll but it can be done. I couldn’t think of a one-size fits\nall solution to cover every use-case so I purposely kept things simple. You can\ncertainly hack something together that would meet your specific needs.</p>\n<p>You’ll likely have to hard code some of the navigation lists rather than relying\non data files for all of the menus. Unless you want to string together some\ncrazy Liquid spaghetti code to do it.</p>\n<p>I’d Google around for some ideas. I know I’ve seen a blog post or two with ways\nof dealing with tiered and dynamic navigations in Jekyll.</p>"}}]}},"pageContext":{"next":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/procreate-paintings/april-c-portrait/","title":"Messy paint across the scalp","categories":["procreate-paintings"],"tags":["Procreate","portrait","illustration","Sktchy","time lapse"]},"fileAbsolutePath":"/home/28041/opensource/github.com/mmistakes/made-mistakes-gatsby/src/posts/procreate-paintings/april-c-portrait.md"},"previous":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/procreate-paintings/morgan-f-portrait/","title":"Tales of round brushing","categories":["procreate-paintings"],"tags":["Procreate","portrait","illustration","Sktchy","time lapse"]},"fileAbsolutePath":"/home/28041/opensource/github.com/mmistakes/made-mistakes-gatsby/src/posts/procreate-paintings/morgan-f-portrait.md"}}}}